ability.name: Quick-Ripening Herb
ability.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may use this Ability. Choose 1 of your Basic Pokémon in play. If you have a Stage 2 card in your hand that evolves from that Pokémon, put that card onto the Basic Pokémon to evolve it. You can use this Ability during your first turn or on a Pokémon that was put into play this turn.

ability.name: Floral Path to the Sky
ability.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may search your deck for Jumpluff, put this Pokémon and all cards attached to it in the Lost Zone, and put that Jumpluff in its place. Then, shuffle your deck.

ability.name: Fresh Squeezed
ability.text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand onto your Bench during your turn, you may search your deck for up to 3 basic Energy cards and discard them. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Shuckle-GX

ability.name: Protective Shell
ability.text: Prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks from your opponent's Pokémon that have 2 or fewer Energy attached to them.

text: When your Pokémon-GX is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

name: Celebi ◇
text: You can't have more than 1 ◇ card with the same name in your deck. If a ◇ card would go to the discard pile, put it in the Lost Zone instead.

ability.name: Sunshine Grace
ability.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may search your deck for a Grass Pokémon, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Sceptile-GX
text: When your Pokémon-GX is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

ability.name: Hazardous Evolution
ability.text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon during your turn, you may leave your opponent's Active Pokémon Paralyzed and Poisoned. If you do, put 3 damage counters instead of 1 on that Pokémon between turns.

ability.name: Molting
ability.text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon during your turn, you may put a Shedinja from your discard pile onto your Bench.

ability.name: Floral Heal
ability.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may heal 20 damage from your Active Grass Pokémon.

name: Virizion-GX
text: When your Pokémon-GX is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

ability.name: Blazing Energy
ability.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may use this Ability. All Energy attached to your Pokémon are Fire Energy instead of their usual type until the end of your turn. (This includes cards that come into play on this turn.)

name: Magcargo-GX

ability.name: Crushing Charge
ability.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may discard the top card of your deck. If it's a basic Energy card, attach it to 1 of your Pokémon.

text: When your Pokémon-GX is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

ability.name: Wild Dash
ability.text: If your opponent has any Pokémon-GX or Pokémon-EX in play, this Pokémon has no Retreat Cost.

name: Blacephalon-GX
text: When your Pokémon-GX is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

ability.name: Secret Alleyway
ability.text: If you have any Fairy Pokémon in play, this Pokémon has no Retreat Cost.

ability.name: Go for a Swim
ability.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may look at the top 2 cards of your deck and put them back in any order.

ability.name: Mantine Surf
ability.text: If this Pokémon has any Energy attached to it, it has no Retreat Cost.

ability.name: Frozen Flow
ability.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if this Pokémon is your Active Pokémon, you may have your opponent switch their Active Pokémon with 1 of their Benched Pokémon.

name: Suicune-GX

ability.name: Phantom Winds
ability.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if this Pokémon is on your Bench, you may shuffle it and all cards attached to it into your deck.

text: When your Pokémon-GX is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

ability.name: Harmonics
ability.text: Whenever you attach an Energy card from your hand to 1 of your Pokémon, except with an attack, Ability, or Trainer card, attach up to 2 Energy cards to that Pokémon instead of 1.

ability.name: Fluffy Pillow
ability.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if this Pokémon is your Active Pokémon, you may leave your opponent's Active Pokémon Asleep.

ability.name: Unseen Flash
ability.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may put 2 Lightning Energy cards from your hand in the Lost Zone. If you do, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

ability.name: Sprint
ability.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may discard your hand and draw 4 cards.

name: Zeraora-GX

ability.name: Thunderclap Zone
ability.text: Each of your Pokémon that has any Lightning Energy attached to it has no Retreat Cost.

text: When your Pokémon-GX is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

ability.name: DAMAGE
ability.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if this Pokémon is your Active Pokémon, and if there are 66 or more damage counters on your Benched Pokémon, you may use this Ability. If you do, you win this game.

ability.name: HAND
ability.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if this Pokémon is your Active Pokémon, and if you have 35 or more cards in your hand, you may use this Ability. If you do, you win this game.

ability.name: MISSING
ability.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if this Pokémon is your Active Pokémon, and if your opponent has 12 or more Supporter cards in the Lost Zone, you may use this Ability. If you do, you win this game.

ability.name: Shady Tail
ability.text: As long as this Pokémon is on your Bench, (Prism Star) Pokémon in play (both yours and your opponent's) can't attack and have no Abilities.

ability.name: Vessel of Life
ability.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may discard all cards attached to this Pokémon and attach it to 1 of your Pokémon as a Pokémon Tool card. When the Pokémon this card is attached to is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 1 fewer Prize card.

ability.name: Distortion Door
ability.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if this Pokémon is in your discard pile, you may put it onto your Bench. If you do, put 1 damage counter on 2 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon.

name: Sigilyph-GX

ability.name: Mirror Counter
ability.text: If this Pokémon is your Active Pokémon and is damaged by an attack from your opponent's Pokémon-GX or Pokémon-EX (even if this Pokémon is Knocked Out), put damage counters on the Attacking Pokémon equal to the damage done to this Pokémon.

text: When your Pokémon-GX is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

ability.name: Charging Up
ability.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may attach a basic Energy card from your discard pile to this Pokémon.

ability.name: Sturdy
ability.text: If this Pokémon has full HP and would be Knocked Out by damage from an attack, this Pokémon is not Knocked Out, and its remaining HP becomes 10.

ability.name: Submerge
ability.text: As long as this Pokémon is on your Bench, prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks (both yours and your opponent's).

ability.name: Hard Shell Evolution
ability.text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon during your turn, you may prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by your opponent's attacks until the end of your opponent's next turn.

name: Tyranitar-GX

ability.name: Lost Out
ability.text: If your opponent's Pokémon is Knocked Out by damage from this Pokémon's attacks, put that Pokémon and all cards attached to it in the Lost Zone instead of the discard pile.

text: When your Pokémon-GX is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

ability.name: Exoskeleton
ability.text: This Pokémon takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Genesect-GX

ability.name: Double Drive
ability.text: This Pokémon may have up to 2 Pokémon Tool cards attached to it. If it loses this Ability, discard Pokémon Tool cards from it until only 1 remains.

text: When your Pokémon-GX is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

name: Alolan Ninetales-GX

ability.name: Mysterious Guidance
ability.text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon during your turn, you may search your deck for up to 2 Item cards, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

text: When your Pokémon-GX is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

name: Xerneas ◇

ability.name: Path of Life
ability.text: Once during your turn, when this Pokémon moves from your Bench to become your Active Pokémon, you may move any number of Energy from your other Pokémon to it.

text: You can't have more than 1 ◇ card with the same name in your deck. If a ◇ card would go to the discard pile, put it in the Lost Zone instead.

ability.name: Mysterious Buzz
ability.text: As long as this Pokémon is on your Bench, whenever your opponent plays a Supporter card from their hand, prevent all effects of that card done to your Fairy Pokémon in play.

ability.name: Effect Spore
ability.text: If this Pokémon is your Active Pokémon and is damaged by an opponent's attack (even if this Pokémon is Knocked Out), the Attacking Pokémon is now Asleep.

name: Mimikyu-GX
text: When your Pokémon-GX is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

ability.name: Charmed Charm
ability.text: Whenever you attach a Pokémon Tool card that has "Fairy Charm" in its name from your hand to this Pokémon during your turn, you may leave your opponent's Active Pokémon Confused.

ability.name: Happiness Supplement
ability.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may remove a Special Condition from your Active Pokémon.

name: Ditto ◇

ability.name: Almighty Evolution
ability.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may put any Stage 1 card from your hand onto this Pokémon to evolve it. You can't use this Ability during your first turn or the turn this Pokémon was put into play.

text: You can't have more than 1 ◇ card with the same name in your deck. If a ◇ card would go to the discard pile, put it in the Lost Zone instead.

name: Lugia-GX
text: When your Pokémon-GX is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

ability.name: Unit Color 1
ability.text: As long as this Pokémon has Unit Energy GrassFireWater attached to it, it is a Grass, Fire, and Water Pokémon.

ability.name: Unit Color 3
ability.text: As long as this Pokémon has Unit Energy FightingDarknessFairy attached to it, it is a Fighting, Darkness, and Fairy Pokémon.

ability.name: Mountain Pass
ability.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if this Pokémon is in your hand, you may reveal it. If you do, look at the top card of your opponent's deck and put this Pokémon in the Lost Zone. If that card is a Supporter card, you may put it in the Lost Zone. If your opponent has no cards in their deck, you can't use this Ability.
